HEADWORD: Octylene
<hw>Oc"tyl*ene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Oct</ets>ane
+ eth<ets>ylene</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Any one of a
series of metameric hydrocarbons (<chform>C8H16</chform>) of the
ethylene series. In general they are combustible, colorless
liquids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

